The paper deals with the study of graph drawings, specifically k-bend right-angle-crossing (RAC) drawings, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the analysis of the maximum edge-density of 1-bend RAC graphs, which is related to graph theory (cs.DM) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also presents new results on the upper and lower bounds of the maximum edge-density, which is a topic in computational complexity and optimization (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of RAC drawings in information visualization (cs.SI).
